The Telegraph - Calcutta : Sport
		 Saturday, July 31, 2004  IN THE CITY
				 																																																	l Four Syrian referees  Hajjar Basel, Hamdoun Tammam, Hamdoun Mashour and Abo Allo Suleman  will officiate the pre-World Cup match between India and Japan at the Salt Lake Stadium on September 8. It was also learnt that two Goan referees, Franky Fernandez and Raghunath Gosavi will officiate the Mohun Bagan-Mohammedan Sporting match on Sunday. 				 																																																	l George Telegraph signed two foreigners M.C. Francis and Theodre Sunday on Friday. Both Francis and Sunday are strikers. 				 																																																	l Debagram Students Corner (Nadia) beat Coochbehar Municipal Recreation Club 4-0 in a S. P. Roy memorial inter-district club football tournament on Friday. 				 																																																	In another tie, Narayanpur United Club beat DM Recreation Club 2-0. 				 																																																	l Central Railway moved into the semi-finals of the YMCA-organised all-India centennial invitation waterpolo tournament beating Salkia Swimming Association 14-3 at the College Square pool on Friday. In two other matches, Central Swimming Club overcame Delhi Swimming Association 9-2 and Rishra Swimming Club defeated Gujarat Swimming Association 15-5. 				 																																																	l Srerampore Rifle Club with nine gold, nine silver and three bronze medals emerged the champions in the 37th state shooting championships that concluded on Thursday. In the individual category, Kaustav Shah with four golds grabbed the top spot. 				 																																																	FOOTBALL: Super division  Tollygunge Agragami vs Eastern Railway (Rabindra Sarobar); George Telegraph vs Port Trust (BNMC, Salt Lake); CFC vs Wari (East Bengal). 				 																																																	WATERPOLO: ALL India invitation meet at College Square pool from 3 pm.
